903
01:16:24,000 --> 01:16:25,956
l'm all ears.

904
01:16:27,320 --> 01:16:29,276
l'll kill you.

905
01:16:30,360 --> 01:16:33,636
Really? That would be a neat trick.

906
01:16:45,320 --> 01:16:49,108
- Well, cuz.
- Are you still pissed at me?

907
01:16:52,080 --> 01:16:57,438
No. But l should have
taken care of you in Detroit.

908
01:17:03,160 --> 01:17:05,469
When l popped your little buddy.

909
01:17:12,040 --> 01:17:14,190
Goodbye, Mr Foley.

910
01:17:16,080 --> 01:17:18,992
- Have a nice day.
- l'll try.

911
01:17:43,600 --> 01:17:45,556
Damn it.

912
01:17:47,880 --> 01:17:49,836
Oh, boy.

913
01:18:01,280 --> 01:18:04,875
How's that little bump
on the head l gave you in Detroit?

914
01:18:04,960 --> 01:18:07,155
Healed up nice, l hope.

915
01:18:31,880 --> 01:18:33,074
Freeze!

916
01:18:46,000 --> 01:18:46,955
Thanks.

917
01:19:01,680 --> 01:19:06,117
Tell Taggart to check out
the warehouse. l'll explain later.

918
01:19:06,200 --> 01:19:09,078
Sergeant Taggart is here,
he wants to talk to you.

919
01:19:09,160 --> 01:19:10,115
Shit!

920
01:19:10,200 --> 01:19:13,033
Billy, what the hell is going on?

921
01:19:13,120 --> 01:19:17,033
- Sorry, Sarge, l can't talk now.
- What do you mean?

922
01:19:17,120 --> 01:19:21,591
Just check out the warehouse and
please don't say anything to Bogomil.

923
01:19:21,680 --> 01:19:24,148
- He's not transmitting any more.
- Shit.

924
01:19:24,240 --> 01:19:28,438
- What's the matter?
